# PART 6a: MODEL STACK EVALUATOR

## 6a.1 Overview

Three-tier local model stack optimised for RTX 3060 12GB. Benchmarks against real production tasks. Weekly scanner for new models. Monthly auto-benchmark. Tier assignments propagated to all pipelines via static_context.

## 6a.2 Hardware Tier Structure

| Tier | Label | VRAM budget | Model size | Target speed |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| 1 — Hot | Email, routing, classification | ≤ 6 GB | 3–8B | > 60 t/s |
| 2 — Medium | Invoice extraction, report parsing | ≤ 10 GB | 9–14B | > 30 t/s |
| 3 — Heavy | Digest, reconciliation, reasoning | RAM | 34–72B | > 8 t/s |

Hot tier (Tier 1) stays VRAM-resident via `OLLAMA_KEEP_ALIVE="-1"`.

## 6a.3 Recommended Initial Stack

| Tier | Model | Rationale |
|---|---|---|
| Hot | `qwen2.5:7b` | 91% classification accuracy, 89 t/s, 4.4 GB |
| Medium | `phi4:14b` | 94% invoice accuracy, 42 t/s, 8.5 GB |
| Heavy | `llama3.3:70b` | 96% reasoning quality |

## 6a.4 Automation Workflows

- **Workflow A** — Weekly Scanner (Sunday 03:00): scan Ollama library, update model_registry, alert on new models
- **Workflow B** — Monthly Full Benchmark (1st of month 04:00): bench all installed models, generate recommendations
- **Workflow C** — New Model Alert (webhook): auto-pull + quick Tier 1 bench, alert if >3% improvement
- **Workflow D** — Manual Trigger (Phase 1): `POST /webhook/model-evaluator-manual`

